Reasoning: The paper discusses a general model of the sensorimotor loop of an agent interacting with the world, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Markov kernels suggests a focus on control and systems theory (cs.SY), while the discussion of a simplified world model is relevant to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the measure-theoretic approach may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
